# EcoSweep Autonomy — Complete Implementation Plan

> **Goal:** Fix all issues causing imprecise movement, detection loss, and failed pickup — then add enhancements to make autonomous mode significantly more reliable, precise, and robust.
>
> **Files to modify:**
> | # | File | Path |
> |---|------|------|
> | 1 | Bridge (autonomy) | [hardware/pi/ecosweep_manual_final_patched.py](file:///d:/Robot_newcontrol/hardware/pi/ecosweep_manual_final_patched.py) |
> | 2 | YOLO detection | [hardware/pi/phase2/yolo_fpv_stream_optimized.py](file:///d:/Robot_newcontrol/hardware/pi/phase2/yolo_fpv_stream_optimized.py) |
>
> Arduino firmware ([EcoSweep_Master.ino](file:///d:/Robot_newcontrol/hardware/arduino/EcoSweep_Master/EcoSweep_Master.ino)) is **not modified** — all fixes are on the Pi side.

---

## Phase 1 — Critical Motor & Data Fixes (P0)

> These two changes eliminate the two biggest root causes. Apply first.

---

### Change 1.1 — Force Gear 3 during autonomous mode

**Problem:** Arduino default gear is 1 (`gearScale=0.40`), halving all autonomy commands.

#### [MODIFY] [ecosweep_manual_final_patched.py](file:///d:/Robot_newcontrol/hardware/pi/ecosweep_manual_final_patched.py)

**Find** (around line 528–541):
```python
if line.strip() == "MODE:AUTO_ON":
    with auto_lock:
        AUTO_MODE = True
    _log("AUTO_MODE ON - autonomy will drive")
    if arduino:
        _write_arduino(line.strip())
    continue
if line.strip() == "MODE:AUTO_OFF":
    with auto_lock:
        AUTO_MODE = False
    _log("AUTO_MODE OFF - manual control")
    if arduino:
        _write_arduino(line.strip())
    continue
```

**Replace with:**
```python
if line.strip() == "MODE:AUTO_ON":
    with auto_lock:
        AUTO_MODE = True
    _log("AUTO_MODE ON - autonomy will drive")
    _write_arduino("GEAR:3")          # ← NEW: full power for autonomous
    if arduino:
        _write_arduino(line.strip())
    continue
if line.strip() == "MODE:AUTO_OFF":
    with auto_lock:
        AUTO_MODE = False
    _log("AUTO_MODE OFF - manual control")
    _write_arduino("GEAR:1")          # ← NEW: restore default for manual
    if arduino:
        _write_arduino(line.strip())
    continue
```

