## Verification Plan

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These are Python scripts running on a Raspberry Pi controlling physical hardware, so automated unit tests cannot validate real-world behavior. Verification is through **debug logs** and **on-robot testing**.

### Automated Check: Syntax Validation

On the Pi (or any machine with Python 3):
```bash
python3 -m py_compile ecosweep_manual_final_patched.py
python3 -m py_compile phase2/yolo_fpv_stream_optimized.py
```
Both must complete with **no errors**.

### On-Robot Testing (Manual, Step-by-Step)

> Run the bridge in debug mode: `sudo python3 -u ecosweep_manual_final.py 2>&1 | tee /tmp/bridge_test.log`

| Test | How to do it | What to check in logs + behavior |
|------|-------------|-----------------------------------|
| **T1: Gear scales on AUTO_ON** | Toggle Autonomous ON in app | Log shows `GEAR:3` sent before `MODE:AUTO_ON` |
| **T2: Search pattern** | AUTO ON, no objects visible | Robot sweeps left for ~2.5 s, drives forward 0.5 s, sweeps right. Smooth, not jerky. |
| **T3: Approach — object far** | Place bottle 2m away, AUTO ON | Robot turns toward bottle (`APPROACH_FAR`), stops turning when centered, drives forward. Log shows `AUTO APPROACH_FAR bbox_cx=... err=... turn=...` |
| **T4: Stop-turn-go** | Place bottle far to the side | Robot should stop forward movement and rotate in place until centered, then drive forward. |
| **T5: No oscillation** | Watch robot approach a bottle head-on | Smooth approach, no left-right jitter. The derivative term should dampen it. |
| **T6: Detection loss recovery** | Briefly cover the camera (0.5 s) during approach | Robot should coast gently (grace period) then resume approach. Should NOT stop-go-stop jerkily. |
| **T7: Pickup sequence** | Let robot approach until close | Log should show `PICKUP: starting full sequence`. Arm opens → lowers → forearm extends → creep → close → retract → raise → rotate → release → return → home. |
| **T8: AUTO OFF restores gear** | Toggle Autonomous OFF | Log shows `GEAR:1` sent. Manual joystick works at normal speed. |
| **T9: YOLO crash resilience** | Kill YOLO process during AUTO | After 1 s of stale data, robot should go to SEARCH. After 5 s, log shows `WARNING: YOLO detection file...` |
| **T10: Pickup retry** | If robot grips but misses, watch | If object is still detected post-pickup, robot should retry approach once before giving up |

### Checklist After Testing

- [ ] T1 passes — gear scales correctly
- [ ] T2 passes — smooth search sweep
- [ ] T3 passes — approaches directly toward object
- [ ] T4 passes — stop-turn-go works at large offsets
- [ ] T5 passes — no oscillation during approach
- [ ] T6 passes — graceful detection loss handling
- [ ] T7 passes — full arm sequence executes
- [ ] T8 passes — manual control restored
- [ ] T9 passes — stale detection handled
- [ ] T10 passes — pickup retry works

### Items Requiring Physical Calibration

| Parameter | How to calibrate |
|-----------|-----------------|
| `TURN_LEFT_SIGN` / `TURN_RIGHT_SIGN` | Object on left → if robot turns right, flip to `-1` |
| `PROPORTIONAL_GAIN` | If oscillating: lower to 0.6. If sluggish: raise to 1.0 |
| `PICKUP_ARM_DOWN_S` | Watch arm descend — increase if it doesn't reach ground |
| `PICKUP_FOREARM_FORWARD_S` | Watch forearm extend — increase if gripper doesn't reach object |
| `PICKUP_GRIP_CLOSE_S` | Increase if object slips out |
| `PICKUP_BBOX_MIN` | Place object at arm-reach distance, read `bbox_area` from debug log, set to that value −20% |
